com:
Are these a trap? I consistently see them for $10000 to $15000 on import sites and even marketplace and craigslist.

How can they be so low when the second and third generation cars are two to three times as much? Are they more prone to crank walk? Rust? Is the handling that much worse without AYC? Fakes made from other Lancers? Insurance????

Please tell me. I want one super bad, but I don't want to buy one and instantly get fucked over by some weird factor I couldn't find in a buyers guide or old forum and end up with 1240kg pile of old kamikaze parts melted into the shape of a turbo sedan that I can't drive.

last_replies.name: Anonymous
last_replies.com:
>Are they a trap

Yes, the transmissions are NLA (think gears/synchros) and they have chronic roof rust on all of them where the roofs rust where the skin is epoxied onto the supports. Also really bad floor pan rust.

https://www.par-engineering.com/product/5m33ss-set-lancer-evolution-13-1st4th-synchromesh-engagement-gearset/

Evo 1-3 transmissions are way weaker than Evo 4-9

>Are they prone to crankwalk

No, that's a 1996 Mitsubishi problem (Evo 4 and DSM). Bigger concern is finding good core blocks/cranks (has to be a 7-Bolt 1995 and older). A 7 Bolt Mitsu Oil Pump is $350.

>Is the handling that much worse

AYC is a meme, the bigger problem is their lack of ability to fit larger tire sizing than 215s, 4x114.3 lug pattern, and lack of decent suspension options vs Evos 4-9.

A cheap Evo is the most expensive Evo and this will turn you into a expert mechanic after a year (or as soon as your engine shits itself....figure 350-370~ whp is the limit which is easy to reach on a stock turbo)

Its cheap because the hype for 1992-1995 cars is dying down and everyone wants Evo 4s and soon Evos 5-6. Plus the market for sports cars is going down and you can still get a LHD 8/9 for $25-30k. A Evo 2/3 is just a really nice DSM in comparison. I predict Evo 5/6 to sell for $28-40k when legal.

Look up Evo 123 owners club on Facebook or evo123.net for info. Evos are painfully expensive and a "cheap" one is still gonna be a restoration project of a 25 y/o sports car that wasn't meant to last more than 10 years. On the plus side lots of parts from Malaysia because they love Evo 1-3s due to commonality with Protons.
